{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"I'd like to share with you a discovery that I made a few months ago"},{"time":7000,"text":"while writing an article for Italian Wired."},{"time":10000,"text":"I always keep my thesaurus handy whenever I'm writing anything,"},{"time":13000,"text":"but I'd already finished editing the piece,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and I realized that I had never once in my life"},{"time":19000,"text":"looked up the word \"disabled\" to see what I'd find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"Let me read you the entry."},{"time":26000,"text":"\"Disabled, adjective: crippled, helpless, useless, wrecked,"},{"time":34000,"text":"stalled, maimed, wounded, mangled, lame, mutilated,"},{"time":41000,"text":"run-down, worn-out, weakened, impotent, castrated, paralyzed, handicapped,"},{"time":51000,"text":"senile, decrepit, laid-up, done-up, done-for, done-in"},{"time":57000,"text":"cracked-up, counted-out;"},{"time":61000,"text":"see also hurt, useless and weak."},{"time":65000,"text":"Antonyms, healthy, strong, capable.\""},{"time":71000,"text":"I was reading this list out loud to a friend and at first was laughing,"},{"time":75000,"text":"it was so ludicrous,"},{"time":77000,"text":"but I'd just gotten past \"mangled,\" and my voice broke,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and I had to stop and collect myself"},{"time":85000,"text":"from the emotional shock and impact that the assault from these words unleashed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"You know, of course, this is my raggedy old thesaurus"},{"time":98000,"text":"so I'm thinking this must be an ancient print date, right?"},{"time":101000,"text":"But, in fact, the print date was the early 1980s,"},{"time":106000,"text":"when I would have been starting primary school"},{"time":108000,"text":"and forming an understanding of myself outside the family unit"},{"time":112000,"text":"and as related to the other kids and the world around me."},{"time":115000,"text":"And, needless to say, thank God I wasn't using a thesaurus back then."},{"time":120000,"text":"I mean, from this entry, it would seem that I was born into a world"},{"time":126000,"text":"that perceived someone like me"},{"time":128000,"text":"to have nothing positive whatsoever going for them,"},{"time":133000,"text":"when in fact, today I'm celebrated for the opportunities and adventures"},{"time":139000,"text":"my life has procured."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"So, I immediately went to look up the 2009 online edition,"},{"time":147000,"text":"expecting to find a revision worth noting."},{"time":151000,"text":"Here's the updated version of this entry."},{"time":154000,"text":"Unfortunately, it's not much better."},{"time":157000,"text":"I find the last two words under \"Near Antonyms,\" particularly unsettling:"},{"time":163000,"text":"\"whole\" and \"wholesome.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So, it's not just about the words."},{"time":170000,"text":"It's what we believe about people when we name them with these words."},{"time":174000,"text":"It's about the values behind the words, and how we construct those values."},{"time":179000,"text":"Our language affects our thinking and how we view the world"},{"time":183000,"text":"and how we view other people."},{"time":186000,"text":"In fact, many ancient societies, including the Greeks and the Romans,"},{"time":189000,"text":"believed that to utter a curse verbally was so powerful,"},{"time":194000,"text":"because to say the thing out loud brought it into existence."},{"time":200000,"text":"So, what reality do we want to call into existence:"},{"time":205000,"text":"a person who is limited, or a person who's empowered?"},{"time":211000,"text":"By casually doing something as simple as naming a person, a child,"},{"time":217000,"text":"we might be putting lids and casting shadows on their power."},{"time":224000,"text":"Wouldn't we want to open doors for them instead?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"One such person who opened doors for me was my childhood doctor"},{"time":231000,"text":"at the A.I. duPont Institute in Wilmington, Delaware."},{"time":236000,"text":"His name was Dr. Pizzutillo,"},{"time":239000,"text":"an Italian American, whose name, apparently,"},{"time":241000,"text":"was too difficult for most Americans to pronounce,"},{"time":243000,"text":"so he went by Dr. P."},{"time":245000,"text":"And Dr. P always wore really colorful bow ties"},{"time":249000,"text":"and had the very perfect disposition to work with children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"I loved almost everything about my time spent at this hospital,"},{"time":260000,"text":"with the exception of my physical therapy sessions."},{"time":264000,"text":"I had to do what seemed like innumerable repetitions of exercises"},{"time":268000,"text":"with these thick, elastic bands -- different colors,"},{"time":272000,"text":"you know -- to help build up my leg muscles,"},{"time":276000,"text":"and I hated these bands more than anything --"},{"time":278000,"text":"I hated them, had names for them. I hated them."},{"time":281000,"text":"And, you know, I was already bargaining, as a five year-old child,"},{"time":285000,"text":"with Dr. P to try to get out of doing these exercises,"},{"time":288000,"text":"unsuccessfully, of course."},{"time":290000,"text":"And, one day, he came in to my session --"},{"time":295000,"text":"exhaustive and unforgiving, these sessions --"},{"time":299000,"text":"and he said to me, \"Wow. Aimee, you are such a strong and powerful little girl,"},{"time":305000,"text":"I think you're going to break one of those bands."},{"time":308000,"text":"When you do break it, I'm going to give you a hundred bucks.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"Now, of course, this was a simple ploy on Dr. P's part"},{"time":315000,"text":"to get me to do the exercises I didn't want to do"},{"time":318000,"text":"before the prospect of being the richest five-year-old in the second floor ward,"},{"time":323000,"text":"but what he effectively did for me was reshape an awful daily occurrence"},{"time":331000,"text":"into a new and promising experience for me."},{"time":335000,"text":"And I have to wonder today to what extent his vision"},{"time":339000,"text":"and his declaration of me as a strong and powerful little girl"},{"time":345000,"text":"shaped my own view of myself"},{"time":347000,"text":"as an inherently strong, powerful and athletic person well into the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"This is an example of how adults in positions of power"},{"time":356000,"text":"can ignite the power of a child."},{"time":360000,"text":"But, in the previous instances of those thesaurus entries,"},{"time":364000,"text":"our language isn't allowing us to evolve into the reality that we would all want,"},{"time":371000,"text":"the possibility of an individual to see themselves as capable."},{"time":377000,"text":"Our language hasn't caught up with the changes in our society,"},{"time":382000,"text":"many of which have been brought about by technology."},{"time":385000,"text":"Certainly, from a medical standpoint,"},{"time":387000,"text":"my legs, laser surgery for vision impairment,"},{"time":393000,"text":"titanium knees and hip replacements for aging bodies"},{"time":396000,"text":"that are allowing people to more fully engage with their abilities,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and move beyond the limits that nature has imposed on them --"},{"time":405000,"text":"not to mention social networking platforms"},{"time":408000,"text":"allow people to self-identify, to claim their own descriptions of themselves,"},{"time":413000,"text":"so they can go align with global groups of their own choosing."},{"time":418000,"text":"So, perhaps technology is revealing more clearly to us now"},{"time":422000,"text":"what has always been a truth:"},{"time":425000,"text":"that everyone has something rare and powerful to offer our society,"},{"time":433000,"text":"and that the human ability to adapt is our greatest asset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"The human ability to adapt, it's an interesting thing,"},{"time":441000,"text":"because people have continually wanted to talk to me about overcoming adversity,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and I'm going to make an admission:"},{"time":450000,"text":"This phrase never sat right with me,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and I always felt uneasy trying to answer people's questions about it,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and I think I'm starting to figure out why."},{"time":460000,"text":"Implicit in this phrase of \"overcoming adversity\""},{"time":464000,"text":"is the idea that success, or happiness,"},{"time":468000,"text":"is about emerging on the other side of a challenging experience"},{"time":471000,"text":"unscathed or unmarked by the experience,"},{"time":476000,"text":"as if my successes in life have come about from an ability"},{"time":480000,"text":"to sidestep or circumnavigate the presumed pitfalls of a life with prosthetics,"},{"time":485000,"text":"or what other people perceive as my disability."},{"time":488000,"text":"But, in fact, we are changed. We are marked, of course, by a challenge,"},{"time":494000,"text":"whether physically, emotionally or both."},{"time":497000,"text":"And I'm going to suggest that this is a good thing."},{"time":500000,"text":"Adversity isn't an obstacle that we need to get around"},{"time":504000,"text":"in order to resume living our life."},{"time":507000,"text":"It's part of our life."},{"time":510000,"text":"And I tend to think of it like my shadow."},{"time":513000,"text":"Sometimes I see a lot of it, sometimes there's very little,"},{"time":516000,"text":"but it's always with me."},{"time":518000,"text":"And, certainly, I'm not trying to diminish the impact, the weight, of a person's struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"There is adversity and challenge in life,"},{"time":528000,"text":"and it's all very real and relative to every single person,"},{"time":531000,"text":"but the question isn't whether or not you're going to meet adversity,"},{"time":535000,"text":"but how you're going to meet it."},{"time":538000,"text":"So, our responsibility is not simply shielding those we care for from adversity,"},{"time":545000,"text":"but preparing them to meet it well."},{"time":548000,"text":"And we do a disservice to our kids"},{"time":552000,"text":"when we make them feel that they're not equipped to adapt."},{"time":559000,"text":"There's an important difference and distinction"},{"time":562000,"text":"between the objective medical fact of my being an amputee"},{"time":567000,"text":"and the subjective societal opinion of whether or not I'm disabled."},{"time":573000,"text":"And, truthfully, the only real and consistent disability I've had to confront"},{"time":578000,"text":"is the world ever thinking that I could be described by those definitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"In our desire to protect those we care about"},{"time":587000,"text":"by giving them the cold, hard truth about their medical prognosis,"},{"time":591000,"text":"or, indeed, a prognosis on the expected quality of their life,"},{"time":595000,"text":"we have to make sure that we don't put the first brick in a wall"},{"time":599000,"text":"that will actually disable someone."},{"time":604000,"text":"Perhaps the existing model of only looking at what is broken in you"},{"time":609000,"text":"and how do we fix it, serves to be more disabling to the individual"},{"time":613000,"text":"than the pathology itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"By not treating the wholeness of a person,"},{"time":621000,"text":"by not acknowledging their potency,"},{"time":623000,"text":"we are creating another ill on top of whatever natural struggle they might have."},{"time":630000,"text":"We are effectively grading someone's worth to our community."},{"time":636000,"text":"So we need to see through the pathology"},{"time":639000,"text":"and into the range of human capability."},{"time":645000,"text":"And, most importantly, there's a partnership"},{"time":649000,"text":"between those perceived deficiencies"},{"time":651000,"text":"and our greatest creative ability."},{"time":654000,"text":"So it's not about devaluing, or negating, these more trying times"},{"time":659000,"text":"as something we want to avoid or sweep under the rug,"},{"time":663000,"text":"but instead to find those opportunities wrapped in the adversity."},{"time":669000,"text":"So maybe the idea I want to put out there is"},{"time":671000,"text":"not so much overcoming adversity"},{"time":676000,"text":"as it is opening ourselves up to it,"},{"time":680000,"text":"embracing it,"},{"time":683000,"text":"grappling with it,"},{"time":685000,"text":"to use a wrestling term,"},{"time":687000,"text":"maybe even dancing with it."},{"time":691000,"text":"And, perhaps, if we see adversity as natural, consistent and useful,"},{"time":699000,"text":"we're less burdened by the presence of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"This year we celebrate the 200th birthday of Charles Darwin,"},{"time":705000,"text":"and it was 150 years ago, when writing about evolution,"},{"time":709000,"text":"that Darwin illustrated, I think, a truth about the human character."},{"time":714000,"text":"To paraphrase: It's not the strongest of the species that survives,"},{"time":718000,"text":"nor is it the most intelligent that survives;"},{"time":721000,"text":"it is the one that is most adaptable to change."},{"time":726000,"text":"Conflict is the genesis of creation."},{"time":731000,"text":"From Darwin's work, amongst others, we can recognize that"},{"time":734000,"text":"the human ability to survive and flourish"},{"time":739000,"text":"is driven by the struggle of the human spirit through conflict"},{"time":744000,"text":"into transformation."},{"time":746000,"text":"So, again, transformation, adaptation, is our greatest human skill."},{"time":753000,"text":"And, perhaps, until we're tested, we don't know what we're made of."},{"time":759000,"text":"Maybe that's what adversity gives us:"},{"time":761000,"text":"a sense of self, a sense of our own power."},{"time":765000,"text":"So, we can give ourselves a gift."},{"time":768000,"text":"We can re-imagine adversity as something more than just tough times."},{"time":775000,"text":"Maybe we can see it as change."},{"time":778000,"text":"Adversity is just change that we haven't adapted ourselves to yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784000,"text":"I think the greatest adversity that we've created for ourselves"},{"time":787000,"text":"is this idea of normalcy."},{"time":789000,"text":"Now, who's normal?"},{"time":792000,"text":"There's no normal."},{"time":794000,"text":"There's common, there's typical. There's no normal,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and would you want to meet that poor, beige person if they existed?"},{"time":800000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":802000,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":804000,"text":"If we can change this paradigm from one of achieving normalcy"},{"time":809000,"text":"to one of possibility -- or potency, to be even a little bit more dangerous --"},{"time":814000,"text":"we can release the power of so many more children,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and invite them to engage their rare and valuable abilities with the community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"Anthropologists tell us that the one thing"},{"time":828000,"text":"we as humans have always required of our community members"},{"time":831000,"text":"is to be of use, to be able to contribute."},{"time":835000,"text":"There's evidence that Neanderthals, 60,000 years ago,"},{"time":839000,"text":"carried their elderly and those with serious physical injury,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and perhaps it's because the life experience of survival of these people"},{"time":851000,"text":"proved of value to the community."},{"time":853000,"text":"They didn't view these people as broken and useless;"},{"time":858000,"text":"they were seen as rare and valuable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"A few years ago, I was in a food market in the town where I grew up"},{"time":864000,"text":"in that red zone in northeastern Pennsylvania,"},{"time":868000,"text":"and I was standing over a bushel of tomatoes."},{"time":870000,"text":"It was summertime: I had shorts on."},{"time":872000,"text":"I hear this guy, his voice behind me say, \"Well, if it isn't Aimee Mullins.\""},{"time":877000,"text":"And I turn around, and it's this older man. I have no idea who he is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881000,"text":"And I said, \"I'm sorry, sir, have we met? I don't remember meeting you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"He said, \"Well, you wouldn't remember meeting me."},{"time":889000,"text":"I mean, when we met I was delivering you from your mother's womb.\""},{"time":892000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":894000,"text":"Oh, that guy."},{"time":897000,"text":"And, but of course, actually, it did click."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"This man was Dr. Kean,"},{"time":902000,"text":"a man that I had only known about through my mother's stories of that day,"},{"time":906000,"text":"because, of course, typical fashion, I arrived late for my birthday by two weeks."},{"time":912000,"text":"And so my mother's prenatal physician had gone on vacation,"},{"time":916000,"text":"so the man who delivered me was a complete stranger to my parents."},{"time":921000,"text":"And, because I was born without the fibula bones,"},{"time":924000,"text":"and had feet turned in, and a few toes in this foot and a few toes in that,"},{"time":927000,"text":"he had to be the bearer -- this stranger had to be the bearer of bad news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"He said to me, \"I had to give this prognosis to your parents"},{"time":936000,"text":"that you would never walk,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and you would never have the kind of mobility that other kids have"},{"time":942000,"text":"or any kind of life of independence,"},{"time":944000,"text":"and you've been making liar out of me ever since.\""},{"time":946000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":948000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":954000,"text":"The extraordinary thing is that he said he had saved"},{"time":958000,"text":"newspaper clippings throughout my whole childhood,"},{"time":961000,"text":"whether winning a second grade spelling bee,"},{"time":963000,"text":"marching with the Girl Scouts, you know, the Halloween parade,"},{"time":966000,"text":"winning my college scholarship, or any of my sports victories,"},{"time":971000,"text":"and he was using it, and integrating it into teaching resident students,"},{"time":977000,"text":"med students from Hahnemann Medical School and Hershey Medical School."},{"time":982000,"text":"And he called this part of the course the X Factor,"},{"time":985000,"text":"the potential of the human will."},{"time":988000,"text":"No prognosis can account for how powerful this could be"},{"time":992000,"text":"as a determinant in the quality of someone's life."},{"time":996000,"text":"And Dr. Kean went on to tell me,"},{"time":999000,"text":"he said, \"In my experience, unless repeatedly told otherwise,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and even if given a modicum of support,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"if left to their own devices, a child will achieve.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017000,"text":"See, Dr. Kean made that shift in thinking."},{"time":1021000,"text":"He understood that there's a difference between the medical condition"},{"time":1024000,"text":"and what someone might do with it."},{"time":1027000,"text":"And there's been a shift in my thinking over time,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"in that, if you had asked me at 15 years old,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"if I would have traded prosthetics for flesh-and-bone legs,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"I wouldn't have hesitated for a second."},{"time":1041000,"text":"I aspired to that kind of normalcy back then."},{"time":1047000,"text":"But if you ask me today, I'm not so sure."},{"time":1050000,"text":"And it's because of the experiences I've had with them,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"not in spite of the experiences I've had with them."},{"time":1061000,"text":"And perhaps this shift in me has happened"},{"time":1064000,"text":"because I've been exposed to more people who have opened doors for me"},{"time":1069000,"text":"than those who have put lids and cast shadows on me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076000,"text":"See, all you really need is one person"},{"time":1078000,"text":"to show you the epiphany of your own power, and you're off."},{"time":1083000,"text":"If you can hand somebody the key to their own power --"},{"time":1088000,"text":"the human spirit is so receptive -- if you can do that"},{"time":1090000,"text":"and open a door for someone at a crucial moment,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"you are educating them in the best sense."},{"time":1096000,"text":"You're teaching them to open doors for themselves."},{"time":1101000,"text":"In fact, the exact meaning of the word \"educate\""},{"time":1107000,"text":"comes from the root word \"educe.\""},{"time":1109000,"text":"It means \"to bring forth what is within,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"to bring out potential.\""},{"time":1115000,"text":"So again, which potential do we want to bring out?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1120000,"text":"There was a case study done in 1960s Britain,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"when they were moving from grammar schools to comprehensive schools."},{"time":1128000,"text":"It's called the streaming trials. We call it \"tracking\" here in the States."},{"time":1131000,"text":"It's separating students from A, B, C, D and so on."},{"time":1136000,"text":"And the \"A students\" get the tougher curriculum, the best teachers, etc."},{"time":1141000,"text":"Well, they took, over a three-month period,"},{"time":1143000,"text":"D-level students, gave them A's,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"told them they were \"A's,\" told them they were bright,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"and at the end of this three-month period,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"they were performing at A-level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154000,"text":"And, of course, the heartbreaking, flip side of this study,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"is that they took the \"A students\" and told them they were \"D's.\""},{"time":1162000,"text":"And that's what happened at the end of that three-month period."},{"time":1165000,"text":"Those who were still around in school, besides the people who had dropped out."},{"time":1171000,"text":"A crucial part of this case study was that the teachers were duped too."},{"time":1180000,"text":"The teachers didn't know a switch had been made."},{"time":1182000,"text":"They were simply told, \"These are the 'A-students,' these are the 'D-students.'\""},{"time":1186000,"text":"And that's how they went about teaching them and treating them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1192000,"text":"So, I think that the only true disability is a crushed spirit,"},{"time":1201000,"text":"a spirit that's been crushed doesn't have hope,"},{"time":1206000,"text":"it doesn't see beauty,"},{"time":1208000,"text":"it no longer has our natural, childlike curiosity"},{"time":1214000,"text":"and our innate ability to imagine."},{"time":1217000,"text":"If instead, we can bolster a human spirit to keep hope,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"to see beauty in themselves and others,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"to be curious and imaginative,"},{"time":1229000,"text":"then we are truly using our power well."},{"time":1233000,"text":"When a spirit has those qualities, we are able to create new realities"},{"time":1239000,"text":"and new ways of being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1242000,"text":"I'd like to leave you with a poem"},{"time":1244000,"text":"by a fourteenth-century Persian poet named Hafiz"},{"time":1248000,"text":"that my friend, Jacques Dembois told me about,"},{"time":1251000,"text":"and the poem is called \"The God Who Only Knows Four Words\":"},{"time":1256000,"text":"\"Every child has known God,"},{"time":1260000,"text":"not the God of names,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"not the God of don'ts,"},{"time":1265000,"text":"but the God who only knows four words and keeps repeating them,"},{"time":1270000,"text":"saying, 'Come dance with me."},{"time":1277000,"text":"Come, dance with me. Come, dance with me.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1280000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1282000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}